@node "Intro" "Introduction"


                             Introduction


    MEM Alert is a small program I coded (with CanDo3) that happily sits
    in the background and yells if your memory is below a certain level.

    That level is determined either by using the built in slider, or
    setting a MEMSIZE tooltype.

    Once you've set the memory level, you can happily ignore MEM Alert
    and do whatever you want.

    When/If your memory falls below the set level, a voice will shout
    out "Memory Alert.!" until you either activate VMM , shut down
    enough applications to raise the memory level or adjust the slider.
    

    @{"ReturnÝtoÝMainÝMenu" link "Main" 0}
@endnode

@node "History" "History"


                          MEM Alert History
                          -----------------


    V0.1   * Small window with memory level locked at 3MB.

           I was also having trouble getting the util to constantly
           check the memory, without it eating too many cpu cycles.


    V0.3   * Added a memory readout and finished the memory scanning
             Routine.

    V0.5þ  * First Released Test Version


    V0.6þ  * Special version for people with BAGS of mem.
           * The ugly buttons were removed and a nice slider added.
             with settings from 5MB up to 100MB (in 5MB increments)

             I liked the slider so much that its going into the next
             version instead of the ugly buttons.

             Thanks to Bob Tracy (on the IML) for the idea to do a
             version of MEM Alert for people with loads of mem.
             (I hate you people...:)

    V0.7þ  * Slight alterations only, nothing visible.
             Routines tidied up a bit and general optimization.

    V0.8þ  * Buttons gone and a nice slider replaced them.
             Looks much nicer and a slider is fun to play with. :)

           * Added a cycle gadget to select between modes.
             Total or Fast. (so MEM Alert monitors either all your mem
             or just your fast mem.)
             (I didn't see the point of adding a chip mem option at
              this point)

             Thanks to Andy Kinsella (on the IML)
             for the Fast/Total idea.

    V0.9þ  * TOOLTYPES ADDED...!!  (this is a major breakthrough as I
             couldn't work out how to do it, but after hours of puzzling
             I sussed it.

           * MEMSIZE and MEMTYPE Tooltypes so far.


    V0.91þ * Small bug squashed..!
             No one reported it, but I accidently had snoopdos3 loaded
             when I loaded MEM Alert, and there was a nasty little
             problem.  MEM Alert kept reading the "topaz" font, each
             time it updated the memory reading.

             UGH..! what a horrible thing to do..!
             I altered the code to read the font only once.
             (when MEM Alert is first run.)

    @{"ReturnÝtoÝMainÝMenu" link "Main" 0}
@endnode

