@node "Usage" "Usage"


                                @{b}@{u}Usage@{ub}@{uu}


 Just click on the icon and MEM Alert will load with the default settings.

 The slider sets the alert level of memory, the cycle gadget sets the mode
 Fast - to watch fast mem only, or Total - to watch all memory.

 The defaults can be altered to suit yourself by using tooltypes.
 Just click once on the icon and either hit right amiga+i or select
 Information of the Icon menu.

 Either way, you'll get a window with a picture of the icon in it.
 Now if you click on the NEW button to add a new tooltype and type

 MEMTYPE=FAST to set the default mode to fast, or
 MEMTYPE=TOTAL to set the default mode to total.

 after that, press return and click on NEW again, to add another
 tooltype. This time we'll add a MEMSIZE tooltype to set the initial
 slider position.

 You can set anything from 2MB up to 20MB, in steps of 2.

 Examples:

 MEMSIZE=4MB  (to set the slider at 4mb)
 MEMSIZE=14MB (to set the slider at 14mb)

 Its pretty simple, the only things you have to remember are:

 1 - Spell it Correctly (MEMSIZE=4M will not work, neither will
                        MEMTYPE=Fast) Use uppercase only.

 2 - Don't change the name of MEMAlert, as that will cause problems
     (MEMAlert looks for MEMAlert.info on loading, so if you rename
     it to MA.info, the tooltypes will not be loaded.)



 @{"ReturnÝtoÝMainÝMenu" link "Main" 0}
@endnode

